Preheat your #oven{} to 200°C. Bring a large #saucepan{} of water to the boil with @salt{1/2%tsp} for the potatoes.

Peel the @Baking Potato{1}, chop them into 1cm chunks. When boiling add the potatoes and cook until you can easily slip a knife through, ~{10-15%mins}.

When the potatoes have been cooking for ~{5%minutes}, reserve some of the potato cooking water.

Peel @garlic clove{1}, wrap in @foil{} with a drizzle of @olive oil{}, roast in the oven for ~{10%mins}.

Peel and grate the @garlic clove{1} (or use a #garlic press{}).

Trim the @spring onion{1} then slice thinly.

Add the @red wine vinegar{12%ml} to a medium sized #bowl{} along with a pinch of @sugar{pinch} and @olive oil{} for the dressing. Mix together and set aside.

Heat a drizzle of @olive oil{} in a #frying pan{} on high heat. When the oil is hot, add the @British Beef Mince{240%g} and cook until browned, ~{5-6%mins}.

Whilst the mince cooks, remove the roasted garlic from the oven, crush into a paste with the back of a #fork{}.

Add the @Low Fat Natural Yoghurt{75%g} to a small bowl and stir in the crushed garlic. Season with @salt{} and @pepper{} and set aside.

Once the mince is cooked, drain off any excess fat and season with @salt{} and @pepper{}.

Return the frying pan with the mince to medium-high heat, add half the @Nigella Seeds{1}, remaining garlic, @Tomato Puree{30%g} and @North Indian Style Spice Mix{1}. Cook stirring frequently for ~{1%minute}.

Pour in the reserved potato water and stir in the @Beef Stock Paste{10%g}, bring to the boil and simmer until the mixture has thickened, ~{3-4%mins}.

> Add a splash of water if the mix is too dry.

Once the potatoes are cooked, drain them in a #colander{}. Carefully stir the potato chunks into the pan with the beef, taste and season with @salt{} and @pepper{}.

Place the @Plain Naans{2} in the oven and bake until toasted and golden, ~{2-3%mins}.

Add the @Baby Gem Lettuce{1}(leaves) to dressing toss to coat.

Share the naans between your plates.

Serve the beef on top of the naan with a handful of salad on top.

Dollop over the garlicky yogurt, sprinkle with the remaining nigella seeds and spring onion. Enjoy!